CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in New Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 12, 1970, pg. 20 reads: "Emergency Meds In Action - This trio of Emergency Medical Technicians, representative of a large number who have received training through the Freedom House Enterprise program, demonstrate the action, which is their usual routine as they respond to round-the-clock emergency calls between lie and death in community.  Walter Brown, right, is crew chief and supervisor of the day shift.  Harvey Gandy, left, and Raymond Pridgen, stand ready to take the portable bed to service the next ambulance patient. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Freedom House emergency medical technicians Raymond Pridgen in driver seat, Harvey Gandy, and Walter Brown wearing beard, posed with ambulance near Presbyterian Hospital, Oakland
